Functions in the Peripheral Lib:
- peripheral.isPresent(side)
	* checks if a peripheral is on the given side
	* return values:
		- boolean indicating if there's a peripheral on that side (boolean)
	* parameters:
		- side: the side to check (string)
- peripheral.getType(side)
	* gets the type of a peripheral
	* return values:
		- the peripheral type (string)
	* parameters:
		- side: the side of the peripheral (string)
- peripheral.getMethods(side)
	* gets a list of the peripheral methods
	* return values:
		- list of methods (table)
	* parameters:
		- side: the side of the peripheral (string)
- peripheral.call(side, method, args)
	* calls a method on the peripheral
	* return values:
		- any values returned by the peripheral method
	* parameters:
		- side: the side of the peripheral (string)
		- method: the method name (string)
		- args: the arguments to pass to the method
- peripheral.wrap(side)
	* wraps the peripheral into a table with it's methods
	* return values:
		- wraped peripheral, nil if no peripheral present (table, nil)
	* parameters:
		- side: the side of the peripheral (string)
- peripheral.sideOf(type)
	* searches the side an specific peripheral is in
	* return values:
		- the side of the peripheral, nil if there's no peripheral with that type (string, nil)
	* parameters:
		- type: the type of peripheral to search (string)
- peripheral.isA(side, type)
	* checks if a peripheral is of a certain type
	* return values:
		- boolean indicating if the peripheral is of the given type (boolean)
	* parameters:
		- side: the side of the peripheral to check (string)
		- type: the type to check (string)
- peripheral.[left/right/top/bottom/front/back]()
	* returns the wraped peripheral of the corresponding side
	* return values:
		- the wraped peripheral (table)
- peripheral.all()
	* returns a list of all the wraped peripherals
	* return values:
		- list of peripherals (table)